column4: B. Social engineering attack
column6: D. user awareness

column4: B. RC4
column6: D. AES-256

column2: 13. Which two must be met before SSH can operate normally on a Cisco IOS switch? (Choose two)
column3: A. The switch must be running a k9 (crypto) IOS image.
column4: B. The ip domain-name command must be configured on the switch.
column5: C. IP routing must be enabled on the switch.
column6: D. A console password must be configured on the switch.

column4: B. outsdwde local

16. How does HSRP provide first hop redundancy?
column3: A. It load-balances traffic by assigning the same metric value to more than one route to the same destination m the IP routing table.
column4: B. It load-balances Layer 2 traffic along the path by flooding traffic out all interfaces configured with the same VLAN.
column5: C. It forwards multiple packets to the same destination over different routed links n the data path.
column6: D. It uses a shared virtual MAC and a virtual IP address to a group of routers that serve as the default gateway for hosts on a LAN.

column2: 17. In Which way does a spine-and-leaf architecture allow for scalability in a network when additional access ports are required?
column3: A. A spine switch and a leaf switch can be added with redundant connections between them.
column4: B. A spine switch can be added with at least 40 GB uplinks.
column5: C. A leaf switch can be added with a single connection to a core spine switch.
column6: D. A leaf switch can be added with connections to every spine switch.

column2: 18. Which two actions are performed by the Weighted Random Early Detection mechanism? (Choose two)
column3: A. It drops lower-priority packets before it drops higher-priority packets.
column4: B. It can identify different flows with a high level of granularity.
column5: C. It guarantees the delivery of high-priority packets.
column6: D. It can mitigate congestion by preventing the queue from filling up.
column7: E. It supports protocol discovery.

column2: 19. A network engineer must back up 20 network router configurations globally within a customer environment. Which protocol allows the engineer to perform this function using the Cisco IOS MIB?
column4: B. SNMP
column6: D. ARP

column2: 20. Refer to the exhibit. What is the effect of this configuration?
column3: A. The switch port interface trust state becomes untrusted.
column4: B. The switch port remains administratively down until the interface is connected to another switch.
column5: C. Dynamic ARP inspection is disabled because the ARP ACL is missing.
column6: D. The switch port remains down until it is configured to trust or untrust incoming packets.

column2: 21. A frame that enters a switch fails the Frame Check Sequence. Which two interface counters are incremented? (Choose two)
column4: B. giants
column6: D. CRC
column7: E. input errors

column2: 22. How do TCP and UDP differ in the way that they establish a connection between two endpoints?
column3: A. TCP uses synchronization packets, and UDP uses acknowledgment packets.
column4: B. UDP uses SYN, SYN ACK and FIN bits in the frame header while TCP uses SYN, SYN ACK and ACK bits.
column5: C. UDP provides reliable message transfer and TCP is a connectionless protocol.
column6: D. TCP uses the three-way handshake and UDP does not guarantee message delivery.

column2: 23. When OSPF learns multiple paths to a network, how does it select a route?
column3: A. It multiple the active K value by 256 to calculate the route with the lowest metric.
column4: B. For each existing interface, it adds the metric from the source router to the destination to calculate the route with the lowest bandwidth.
column5: C. It divides a reference bandwidth of 100 Mbps by the actual bandwidth of the existing interface to calculate the router with the lowest cost.
column6: D. It count the number of hops between the source router and the destination to determine the router with the lowest metric.

column2: 24. Refer to the exhibit. Which password must an engineer use to enter the enable mode?
column4: B. default
column6: D. cisco123

column2: 25. Which configuration is needed to generate an RSA key for SSH on a router?
column3: A. Configure the version of SSH.
column4: B. Configure VTY access.
column5: C. Create a user with a password.
column6: D. Assign a DNS domain name.

column2: 26. Which output displays a JSON data representation?
column4: B. Option B
column6: D. Option D

column2: 27. What is the primary different between AAA authentication and authorization?
column3: A. Authentication verifies a username and password, and authorization handles the communication between the authentication agent and the user database.
column4: B. Authentication identifies a user who is attempting to access a system, and authorization validates the users password.
column5: C. Authentication identifies and verifies a user who is attempting to access a system, and authorization controls the tasks the user can perform.
column6: D. Authentication controls the system processes a user can access and authorization logs the activities the user initiates.

column2: 28. A Cisco IP phone receive untagged data traffic from an attached PC. Which action is taken by the phone?
column3: A. It allows the traffic to pass through unchanged.
column4: B. It drops the traffic.
column5: C. It tags the traffic with the default VLAN.
column6: D. It tags the traffic with the native VLAN.

column2: 29. An engineer must configure a/30 subnet between two routers. Which usable IP address and subnet mask combination meets this criteria?
column3: A. interface e0/0   description to HQ-A370:98968 ip address 10.2.1.3 255.255.255.252
column4: B. interface e0/0  description to HQ-A370:98968  ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.248
column5: C. interface e0/0  description to HQ-A370:98968  ip address 172.16.1.4 255.255.255.248

column2: 30. What is a benefit of using a Cisco Wireless LAN Controller?
column3: A. Central AP management requires more complex configurations.
column4: B. Unique SSIDs cannot use the same authentication method.
column5: C. It supports autonomous and lightweight APs.
column6: D. It eliminates the need to configure each access point individually.

column2: 31. What are two characteristics of a controller-based network? (Choose two)
column3: A. The administrator can make configuration updates from the CLI.
column4: B. It uses northbound and southbound APIs to communicate between architectural layers.
column5: C. It moves the control plane to a central point.
column6: D. It decentralizes the control plane, which allows each device to make its own forwarding decisions.
column7: E. It uses Telnet to report system issues.

column2: 32. Which attribute does a router use to select the best path when two or more different routes to the same destination exist from two different routing protocols?
column4: B. metric
column6: D. hop count

column2: 33. Refer to Exhibit. How does SW2 interact with other switches in this VTP domain?
column3: A. It processes VTP updates from any VTP clients on the network on its access ports.
column4: B. It receives updates from all VTP servers and forwards all locally configured VLANs out all trunk ports.
column5: C. It forwards only the VTP advertisements that it receives on its trunk ports.
column6: D. It transmits and processes VTP updates from any VTP Clients on the network on its trunk ports.

column2: 45. Which two actions influence the EIGRP route selection process? (Choose two)

column2: 66. Which two outcomes are predictable behaviors for HSRP? (Choose two)
column3: A. The two routers share a virtual IP address that is used as the default gateway for devices on the LAN.
column4: B. The two routers negotiate one router as the active router and the other as the standby router.
column5: C. Each router has a different IP address both routers act as the default gateway on the LAN, and traffic is load balanced between them.
column6: D. The two routers synchronize configurations to provide consistent packet forwarding.
column7: E. The two routed share the same IP address, and default gateway traffic is load-balanced between them.

column2: 67. Which action is taken by a switch port enabled for PoE power classification override?

column4: B. As power usage on a PoE switch port is checked data flow to the connected device is temporarily paused.
column5: C. If a switch determines that a device is using less than the minimum configured power it assumes the device has failed and disconnects.
column6: D. If a monitored port exceeds the maximum administrative value for power, the port is shutdown and err disabled.

column6: D. Configure the ipv6 route 2023::/126 2012::2 command on the Atlanta router.
column7: E. Configure the ipv6 route 2012::/126 2023::2 command on the Washington router.

column2: 73. When a floating static route is configured, which action ensures that the backup route is used when the primary route fails?

column5: C. The floating static route must have a lower administrative distance than the primary route so it is used as a backup.
